{#-
  VHS tape template (M5). Rendered by distill.write_artifacts with
  trim_blocks + lstrip_blocks, context: tape = list[TapeCommand].

  The tape IS the step_by_step.md on camera: it executes every guide step
  for real inside the base image (which layers toolchains on top of the
  official VHS image). The hidden preamble moves the session into the empty
  /work directory so the guide's own `git clone ... .` works.

  Pacing: after each command, `Wait` blocks until the shell prompt returns
  (i.e. the command finished — builds included; WaitTimeout bounds it), then
  a short Sleep gives viewers time to read the output. Wait+Screen on output
  text is deliberately NOT used: it only matches the visible buffer, so any
  pattern in longer-than-one-screen output scrolls away and times out.

  Quoting: VHS string literals do not support backslash escapes; the
  vhs_quote filter picks a delimiter (" then ` then ') the text doesn't
  contain.
-#}
Output demo.mp4

Set FontSize 18
Set Width 1200
Set Height 700
Set Framerate 24
Set TypingSpeed 50ms
Set Theme "Catppuccin Mocha"
Set Shell bash
Set WaitTimeout 600s

Hide
Type "cd /work && clear"
Enter
Wait
Show

{% for tc in tape %}
{% if tc.comment %}
Type {{ ('# ' + tc.comment) | vhs_quote }}
Enter
Sleep 800ms
{% endif %}
{% if tc.hide %}
Hide
{% endif %}
{% if tc.lines %}
{#- heredoc / multi-line: type each line, Enter between, so it plays on camera -#}
{% for ln in tc.lines %}
Type {{ ln | vhs_quote }}
Enter
{% endfor %}
Wait
Sleep {{ tc.sleep_after_s }}s
{% else %}
Type {{ tc.cmd | vhs_quote }}
Enter
Wait
Sleep {{ tc.sleep_after_s }}s
{% endif %}
{% if tc.hide %}
Show
{% endif %}

{% endfor %}
Sleep 3s
